# UI Standards

Interfaces must feel professional, modern, simple, predictable, and consistent.

## Hierarchy

Every screen must make obvious: primary action, secondary actions, important info, supporting info, danger actions.

## Page chrome

- Clear page title (+ short description when needed)
- Primary CTA in a predictable place
- Consistent margins and spacing scale (no random values)
- Balanced whitespace — crowded UI is a bug

## Typography & color

- Use the design system type scale and semantic colors only
- Color has meaning: primary, success, warning, danger, muted
- Never invent one-off font sizes or hex values when tokens exist

## Components

- Prefer existing design-system / shadcn primitives
- Do not introduce a second visual language
- Cards only when they contain interaction or a clear content unit — not decoration
- Status via pills/badges with semantic colors

## RTL (mandatory for Arabic products)

- Root layout is `dir="rtl"` / `lang="ar"` unless the project says otherwise
- Mirror layout, not only text — swap column widths and start/end spacing
- Keep LTR islands for phones, emails, codes, URLs (`dir="ltr"`)

## Dark mode

Design contrast intentionally. Do not ship washed-out or inverted accidents.

## Density

Ops/ERP UIs: clear and efficient. Marketing/landing: brand-led (see project rules). Never mix the two aesthetics on the same surface.
